resolution: "Completed the 2026-06-25 PM ecosystem review: current work is tracked under pm-57vh; four sub-agent lanes are closed with evidence; product fixes pm-bhtx and pm-7o0s are closed; non-release-safe historical cleanup is represented as open tracker-only backlog; PR #361 passed all GitHub checks and CodeRabbit produced no actionable comments."
expected_result: "Tracker reflects the current PM ecosystem without duplicate new items, product reliability fixes are verified, GitHub checks are green, available AI bot feedback is addressed or documented, Sentry/telemetry are recent and non-blocking, and the branch is ready to merge."
actual_result: "All local gates passed, GitHub checks are green, CodeRabbit found no actionable comments, quota/setup-limited bots produced no actionable findings, Sentry has 0 critical/high blockers, telemetry required-mode is ok, and PR #361 is merge-ready pending final tracking commit/check loop."
comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T04:44:17.429Z",codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625,"Duplicate check before create: ran pm search \"2026-06-25 PM ecosystem taxonomy backlog normalization context management\" --status all --limit 20. The closest prior item is closed pm-8u2a from 2026-06-07; no live duplicate exists for this 2026-06-25 normalization/review loop."
  "2026-06-25T05:09:13.145Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Evidence: tracker governance normalization pass reduced metadata close_reason gaps from 18 to 0 using title/description/resolution context. validate --check-files now reports 0 missing linked paths and 0 orphaned paths after pm-j8z6 reconciliation. Remaining historical resolution metadata debt is tracked in pm-e9zh to avoid placeholder backfills."
  "2026-06-25T05:21:06.957Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Audit correction after changelog review: broad historical linked-file and stale-container mutations were pruned from this release branch because they touched hundreds of old PM records and caused generated CHANGELOG.md to mis-bucket old work as current. Kept product fixes are pm-bhtx (--status all aggregate sentinel) and pm-7o0s (stats history ENOENT/Sentry PM-CLI-1T). Deferred tracker-only backlog is now explicit in pm-j8z6, pm-psc0, pm-e9zh, pm-y1o4, pm-v37g, pm-a7o4, and pm-bhmk. Current validation baseline after pruning: lifecycle/history/command references ok; file validator warns with 146 missing linked paths and 162 orphaned paths; metadata warns with 24 missing AC/estimate, 18 missing close reasons, 2 duplicate GH code pairs; resolution warns with 253 historical terminal metadata gaps."
  "2026-06-25T05:30:02.151Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Final local evidence before PR: npm install -g . refreshed the global pm binary from this checkout; pnpm build passed; focused tests passed 29/29; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm quality:static passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 250 files / 5068 tests with 100% statements/branches/functions/lines; pnpm changelog:pm:check passed unchanged; pnpm security:scan found no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no known vulnerabilities; pm health --check-only --summary --json ok with warning_count=0; pm validate --check-lifecycle --check-command-references --check-history-drift --json ok with no warnings; pm aggregate --group-by parent --count --completion --include-unparented --status all passed after global refresh; pm stats --storage --json passed; linked pm-bhtx and pm-7o0s tests passed after tracker-context metadata correction; Sentry/telemetry required-mode gate passed with critical=0, high=0, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.82, failures_without_error_code_rows=0."
  "2026-06-25T05:40:56.192Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"PR review/check evidence: PR #361 opened at https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/361. GitHub checks all green on d4f26218: Build foundation, Docs and Skills, CodeQL, compat, coverage, smokes, static, typecheck, Windows regression, and runtime smokes passed; CodeRabbit status passed and comment says no actionable comments were generated. Gemini Code Assist reported daily quota exhausted twice; Sourcery reported weekly diff-character quota exhausted; Codex connector replied that a Codex account/GitHub connector setup is required, so those produced no actionable review findings to fix."
